{age|1996|2|14}} || Right handed || Left-arm [[fast bowling|fast medium]] || colspan=3 {{n/a}} || [[Dhaka Metropolis]] || ODI, T20I || 14 ||align=center| \u2013 \n|-\n| [[Ebadot Hossain]] || {{age|1994|1|7}} || Right handed || Right-arm [[Pace bowling|fast medium]] ||align=center| D || {{yes}} || {{no}} || [[Sylhet Division cricket team|Sylhet Division]] || Test || 96 || align=center| \u2013 \n|-\n! colspan=\"15\" | Spin Bowlers\n|-\n| [[Taijul Islam]] || {{age|1992|2|14}} || Left handed || [[Slow left-arm orthodox]] ||align=center| B / D || colspan=2 {{yes}} || [[Rajshahi Division]] || Test || 12 || align=center| \u2013 \n|-\n| [[Nayeem Hasan]] || {{age|2000|12|2}} || Right handed || Right-arm [[Spin bowling|off break]] ||align=center| D || {{yes}} || {{no}} || [[Chittagong Division cricket team|Chittagong Division]] || Test || 33 || align=center| \u2013 \n|}\n \nThe BCB awards central contracts to its players, its pay graded according to the importance of the player. Players' salaries are as follows:\n* Grade A+ : {{BDTConvert|48|l|lk=yes}} per annum\n* Grade A : {{BDTConvert|36|l}} per annum\n* Grade B : {{BDTConvert|24|l}} per annum\n* Grade C : {{BDTConvert|15|l}} per annum\n* Grade D : {{BDTConvert|12|l}} per annum\n \nIn addition to this, [[Tamim Iqbal]], the ODI captain earns a responsibility bonus of {{BDTConvert|30|k}} per month while [[Mushfiqur Rahim]] is given {{BDTConvert|20|k}} bonus for playing more matches than others.<ref name=\"Contract 2020\"/>\n\n;Match fees\nIn January 2020, BCB increased test match fees by 70% in test cricket as well as ODI and T20I match fees. Players who are in the playing XI get paid {{BDTConvert|6|l}} for each test while they are paid {{BDTConvert|3|l}} for each ODI and {{BDTConvert|2|l}} for each T20I.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Isam |first1=Mohammad |title=BCB increases Test-match fees by over 70% |url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/28470236/bcb-increases-test-match-fees-70 |accessdate=14 January 2020 |work=ESPNcricinfo |date=12 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Coaching staff==\n* Team Manager: {{flagicon|BAN}} [[Khaled Mahmud]]\n* Head Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Russell Domingo]]\n* Batting Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Neil McKenzie]]\n* Spin Bowling Coach: {{flagicon|NZ}} [[Daniel Vettori]]\n* Fast Bowling Coach: {{flagicon|Barbados}} [[Ottis Gibson]]\n* Fielding Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Ryan Cook (cricketer)|Ryan Cook]]\n* Physiotherapist: {{Flagicon|SA}} [[Julian Calefato]]\n* Strength and Conditioning Coach:\n* Performance Analyst: {{flagicon|BAN}} [[Nasir Ahmed (cricketer, born 1964)|Nasir Ahmed]]\n* Team Psychologist:\n* Team Physician: {{flagicon|BAN}} Dr. Debasish Roy Chowdhury\n* Media Manager: {{flagicon|BAN}} Rabeed Imam\n\n==Tournament history==\n''A red box around the year indicates tournaments played within Bangladesh''\n\n===ICC Cricket World Cup===\n{{main|Bangladesh at the Cricket World Cup}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=8|[[Cricket World Cup|World Cup record]]\n|-\n! width=150 |Year\n! width=150 |Round\n! width=50 |Position\n! width=50 |GP\n! width=50 |Win\n! width=50 |Lost\n! width=50 |Tie\n! width=50 |NR\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1975 Cricket World Cup|1975]] ||  colspan=7| Not eligible (Not an ICC Member)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1979 Cricket World Cup|1979]] || colspan=7 rowspan=5| Did not qualify\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} {{flagicon|WAL}} [[1983 Cricket World Cup|1983]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|PAK}} [[1987 Cricket World Cup|1987]] \n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} {{flagicon|NZL}} [[1992 Cricket World Cup|1992]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|PAK}} {{flagicon|SRI}} [[1996 Cricket World Cup|1996]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|UK}} {{flagicon|IRL}} {{flagicon|NED}} [[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]] || rowspan=2| Group stage || 9/12 || 5 || 2 || 3 || 0 || 0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} {{flagicon|ZIM}} {{flagicon|KEN}} [[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]] || 13/14 || 6 || 0 || 5 || 0 || 1\n|- style=\"background:#f2f2f2;\"\n|{{flagicon|WIN}}