ory/_/id/28470236/bcb-increases-test-match-fees-70 |accessdate=14 January 2020 |work=ESPNcricinfo |date=12 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Coaching staff==\n* Head Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Russell Domingo]]\n* Batting Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Neil McKenzie]]\n* Fast Bowling Coach: {{flagicon|Barbados}} [[Ottis Gibson]]\n* Spin Bowling Coach: {{flagicon|NZ}} [[Daniel Vettori]]<ref name=\"Coaches\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cricbuzz.com/cricket-news/109113/bangladesh-appoint-langeveldt-vettori-as-bowling-coaches|title=Bangladesh appoint Langeveldt, Vettori as bowling coaches|website=Cricbuzz|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* Fielding Coach: {{flagicon|RSA}} [[Ryan Cook (cricketer)|Ryan Cook]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/24068606/ryan-cook-named-bangladesh-fielding-consultant|title=Ryan Cook named Bangladesh fielding consultant|date=11 July 2018}}</ref>\n* Strength and Conditioning Coach: {{flagicon|SL}} [[Mario Villavarayan]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/bangladesh/content/story/747873.html |title=Mario Villavarayan as the strength and conditioning coach |date=19 May 2014 |publisher=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref>\n* Team Physiotherapist: {{Flagicon|SA}}/{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Julian Calefato]]\n* Team Psychologist: vacant\n* Team Physician: {{flagicon|BAN}} Dr. Debasish Roy Chowdhury<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/printversion/details/23751 |title=Mash injury jolts Comilla Victorians |newspaper=The Independent |date=21 November 2015 |accessdate=14 June 2016}}</ref>\n* Team Manager: {{flagicon|BAN}} [[Khaled Mahmud]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/cricket/2015/jan/16/bcb-names-mahmud-new-manager |title=BCB names Mahmud as the new Team Manager |work=Dhaka Tribune |accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n* Media Manager: {{flagicon|BAN}} Rabeed Imam<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/story/author.html?author=27 |title=Rabeed Imam |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=10 October 2011}}</ref>\n* Performance Analyst: {{flagicon|BAN}} [[Nasir Ahmed (cricketer, born 1964)|Nasir Ahmed]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.goalbangladesh.com/2015/07/07/performance-analyst-world-football-and-bangladesh/ |title=Nasir Ahmed Nasu has worked successively with Bangladesh national cricket team for 15 years |publisher=Goal Bangladesh |accessdate=7 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Tournament history==\n''A red box around the year indicates tournaments played within Bangladesh''\n\n===ICC Cricket World Cup===\n{{main|Bangladesh at the Cricket World Cup}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=8|[[Cricket World Cup|World Cup record]]\n|-\n! width=150 |Year\n! width=150 |Round\n! width=50 |Position\n! width=50 |GP\n! width=50 |Win\n! width=50 |Lost\n! width=50 |Tie\n! width=50 |NR\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1975 Cricket World Cup|1975]] ||  colspan=7| Not eligible (Not an ICC Member)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1979 Cricket World Cup|1979]] || colspan=7 rowspan=5| Did not qualify\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} {{flagicon|WAL}} [[1983 Cricket World Cup|1983]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|PAK}} [[1987 Cricket World Cup|1987]] \n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} {{flagicon|NZL}} [[1992 Cricket World Cup|1992]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|PAK}} {{flagicon|SRI}} [[1996 Cricket World Cup|1996]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|UK}} {{flagicon|IRL}} {{flagicon|NED}} [[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]] || rowspan=2| Group stage || 9/12 || 5 || 2 || 3 || 0 || 0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} {{flagicon|ZIM}} {{flagicon|KEN}} [[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]] || 13/14 || 6 || 0 || 5 || 0 || 1\n|- style=\"background:#f2f2f2;\"\n|{{flagicon|WIN}} [[2007 Cricket World Cup|2007]] || Super Eights || 7/16 || 9 || 3 || 6 || 0 || 0\n|-\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|SRI}} {{flagicon|BAN}} [[2011 Cricket World Cup|2011]] || Group stage || 9/14 || 6 || 3 || 3 || 0 || 0\n|- style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"\n||{{flagicon|AUS}} {{flagicon|NZL}} [[2015 Cricket Worl